ğŸ§ . What are the main features of Terraform?
 Terraform is an Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tool used to build, change, and manage infrastructure safely and efficiently.

1ï¸âƒ£ Multi-Cloud Support
Works with AWS, Azure, GCP, and many other providers

2ï¸âƒ£ State Management
Maintains a state file (terraform.tfstate)
Tracks real infrastructure vs code
Supports remote state (S3, Azure Blob, GCS)

3ï¸âƒ£ Execution Plan (terraform plan)
Shows what will be created, updated, or destroyed
Prevents unexpected changes

7ï¸âƒ£ Modules
Reusable infrastructure components
Helps follow DRY (Donâ€™t Repeat Yourself) principle

8ï¸âƒ£ Provisioners (Optional)
Run scripts or commands after resource creation
Used rarely (not recommended for most cases)

